<subSubSection id="2AC3655CFF9B2477F866F7CA0E050518" lastPageId="51" lastPageNumber="336" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="626636D7FF9B2476F866F7CA055A0814" blockId="50.[1987,2582,1989,2416]" pageId="50" pageNumber="335">O. Thomas described the genus Sminthopsis in 1887. Almost 100 years later, in a major revision, M. Archer not only recognized twelve species of dunnart but also drew attention to several discrete populations and the fact that most recognized species exhibited geographical variation that might constitute different species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="626636D7FF9B2477FAC2F6860A2A0532" blockId="50.[1377,2583,2423,3243]" lastBlockId="51.[167,1383,288,3481]" lastPageId="51" lastPageNumber="336" pageId="50" pageNumber="335">
Subsequent electrophoretic and direct DNA studies have supported his contention. 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476FAC1F66F0AB108DB" box="[1378,1529,2462,2495]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Sminthopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Sminthopsis</taxonomicName>
is the most speciose genus (currently 19 species) of living dasyurid marsupials and, along with its close relatives 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476F826F634077D0882" authorityName="Krefft" authorityYear="1867" box="[1925,2101,2501,2534]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Antechinomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Antechinomys</taxonomicName>
(one species) and Ningau: (three species), and 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476F981F61C09D30B6A" box="[1570,1691,2541,2574]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Planigale" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Planigale</taxonomicName>
(five species) constitutes the clade Sminthopsini. Phylogenetic relationships among species in the 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476F8F6F5E507600B51" authorityName="Archer" authorityYear="1982" box="[1877,2088,2580,2613]" pageId="50" pageNumber="340" rank="tribe" tribe="Sminthopsinae">Sminthopsinae</taxonomicName>
have been the subject of considerable morphological and molecular investigation. A recent genetic phylogeny (several mitochondrial and nuclear genes) failed to support monophyly of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476F634F5920AC90BCF" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Sminthopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Sminthopsis</taxonomicName>
with respect to 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476F9FDF57B08460BCF" authorityName="Krefft" authorityYear="1867" box="[1630,1806,2698,2731]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Antechinomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Antechinomys</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476F8F7F57B08890BCF" box="[1876,1985,2698,2731]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Ningaui" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Ningaui</taxonomicName>
. There were three deeply divergent clades of 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476FA29F543097F0BB7" box="[1418,1591,2738,2771]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Sminthopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Sminthopsis</taxonomicName>
. In the first clade, S. 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476F8D5F54307530BB7" baseAuthorityName="Schlegel" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[1910,2075,2738,2771]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Murexia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longicaudata">longicaudata</taxonomicName>
was sister to A. 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476F6A8F543062C0BB7" baseAuthorityName="Gould" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[2315,2404,2738,2771]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Antechinomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="laniger">laniger</taxonomicName>
(an alliance also obtained from previous morphological analyses where there was good reason to include 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476FA70F4F109CA0A45" authorityName="Krefft" authorityYear="1867" box="[1491,1666,2816,2849]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Antechinomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Antechinomys</taxonomicName>
within 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476F94AF4F108C80A45" box="[1769,1920,2816,2849]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Sminthopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Sminthopsis</taxonomicName>
and also to link it with S. 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476F742F4F106C50A45" baseAuthorityName="Schlegel" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[2273,2445,2816,2849]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Murexia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longicaudata">longicaudata</taxonomicName>
). The second clade was composed of the traditional morphologically based 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476F6BFF4D906ED0A2D" baseAuthorityName="Gould" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[2332,2469,2856,2889]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Sminthopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macroura">Macroura</taxonomicName>
Group: five 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476FA02F4BE09700A14" box="[1441,1592,2895,2928]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Sminthopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Sminthopsis</taxonomicName>
formed a strongly supported clade, which included S. 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476F6C1F4BE05460A14" baseAuthorityName="Gould" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[2402,2574,2895,2928]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Sminthopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crassicaudata">crassicaudata</taxonomicName>
, S. bind, S. 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476FA56F48E09250AFC" baseAuthorityName="Gould" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[1525,1645,2943,2968]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Sminthopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macroura">macroura</taxonomicName>
, S. 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476F93EF48E084F0AFC" authorityName="Archer" authorityYear="1979" box="[1693,1799,2943,2968]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Sminthopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="douglasi">douglasi</taxonomicName>
, and S. 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476F8D7F48E08AD0AFC" baseAuthorityName="de Tarragon" baseAuthorityYear="1847" box="[1908,2021,2943,2968]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Sminthopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="virginiae">virginiae</taxonomicName>
. This clade of five dunnarts was a poorly supported sister to the three species of 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476F828F46F08BF0ADB" box="[1931,2039,2974,3007]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Ningaui" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Ningaui</taxonomicName>
(N. rider, 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476F7DCF46F065D0ADB" authorityName="Archer" authorityYear="1975" box="[2175,2325,2974,3007]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Ningaui" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="344" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="timealeyi">N. timealeyi</taxonomicName>
, and N. yvonneae). This combined clade of the five 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476F880F43408F20A82" box="[1827,1978,3013,3046]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Sminthopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Sminthopsis</taxonomicName>
and three 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476F7F1F43407F60A82" box="[2130,2238,3013,3046]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Ningaui" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Ningaui</taxonomicName>
was positioned as poorly supported sister to a well-supported clade containing the remainder of 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476F623F41C0A8B0D51" pageId="50" pageNumber="335">Sminthopsis species</taxonomicName>
(13 species in the 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476F973F3E508700D51" box="[1744,1848,3092,3125]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Sminthopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="murina">Murina</taxonomicName>
Group). This large dunnart clade contained a wellsupported sister pairing of 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476F94CF3CA08210D38" authorityName="Van Dyck" authorityYear="1986" box="[1775,1897,3131,3164]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Sminthopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="archeri">S. archeri</taxonomicName>
with a clade containing five species: S. munna, S. gilberti, S. 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476F9A9F39A093C0DE0" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[1546,1652,3179,3204]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Sminthopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leucopus">leucopus</taxonomicName>
, S. 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476F906F39A09BC0DE0" authorityName="Archer" authorityYear="1979" box="[1701,1780,3179,3204]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Sminthopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="butleri">butleri</taxonomicName>
, and S. 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9B2476F8C0F39A08930DE0" authorityName="Kitchener, Stoddart &amp; Henry" authorityYear="1984" box="[1891,2011,3179,3204]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Sminthopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="50" pageNumber="335" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dolichura">dolichura</taxonomicName>
. During a 1973 mammal survey of southwestern Papua New Guinea, a number of dunnarts were collected from pitfall traps. A taxonomic reassessment of these animals by S. Van Dyck in 1986 resulted in their description as S. archer: (in honor of paleontologist and taxonomist M. Archer, who had done a considerable amount of taxonomic work on the genus) and led to the discovery that the species also occurred in northern Australia. Indeed,it had been collected as early as 1898 by A. S. Meek and anthropologist D. Thomson in 1933 from the lower Archer River on Cape York Peninsula. Later captures (in the early 1980s) were made from monsoon woodlands near Batavia Landing and Red Beach on north-western Cape York. Following the description of the new S. archer, four of the 13 specimens examined by Van Dyck were transferred to the Queensland Museum, Brisbane. The other nine were registered as S. 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9A2477FD22FD720D9E03C0" authorityName="Van Dyck" authorityYear="1986" box="[641,726,643,676]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Sminthopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="51" pageNumber="336" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="archeri">archeri</taxonomicName>
and held in the Papua New Guinea Museum. New Guinean and northern Queensland S. 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9A2477FCB4FD5B0C2303AF" authorityName="Van Dyck" authorityYear="1986" box="[791,875,682,715]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Sminthopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="51" pageNumber="336" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="archeri">archeri</taxonomicName>
shared dental and foot-pad features that distinguished them from S. 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9A2477FDDAFD230D800397" authorityName="Archer" authorityYear="1979" box="[633,712,722,755]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Sminthopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="51" pageNumber="336" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="butleri">butleri</taxonomicName>
, a congener with which they had been lumped; however, the last documented capture of S. 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9A2477FC84FD080C34027E" authorityName="Van Dyck" authorityYear="1986" box="[807,892,761,794]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Sminthopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="51" pageNumber="336" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="archeri">archeri</taxonomicName>
on Cape York Peninsula occurred in 1993 when a single male was trapped at Iron Range National Park, Queensland. Subsequent targeted searches (Heathlands, Pennefather River, and north-western Cape York) have yielded zero captures. Then, incredibly, in March 2003, an individual was trapped at Blackbraes National Park, 200 km west of Townsville, Queensland, a staggering 1000 km south of the Cape York individuals. This represents a marked biogeographical shift to an upland, dry tropical biome and raised questions of whether or not distribution of S. 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9A2477FDAFFBFC0D29054A" authorityName="Van Dyck" authorityYear="1986" box="[524,609,1037,1070]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Sminthopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="51" pageNumber="336" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="archeri">archeri</taxonomicName>
is naturally fragmented and widespread with naturally low abundance, or perhaps S. 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FF9A2477FDCCFBC40D8C0532" authorityName="Van Dyck" authorityYear="1986" box="[623,708,1077,1110]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Sminthopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="51" pageNumber="336" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="archeri">archeri</taxonomicName>
is in need of further taxonomic investigation.
</paragraph>
